wikipedia_page.main: William George Henderson (25 June 1819 – 24 September 1905) was Dean of Carlisle from 1884 to his death in 1905.

response: The school's first headmaster was William Henderson. A graduate of Magdalen College, Oxford, Henderson was headmaster at the school for ten years from 1852 until 1862. The school's current headmaster is Gareth Hughes, who took up the post in 2021 on a one year basis following the retirement of Alun Watkins. The full list of headmasters of the school is as follows:
*William Henderson, 1st Baron Henderson (1891–1984), English Labour legislator
*William Henderson (Canadian politician) (1916–2006), Canadian politician and judge
*William Henderson (American football) (born 1971), fullback, TV football commentator
*William Henderson (philanthropist) (1826–1904), Scottish shipping merchant, builder of Royal Infirmary
*William Henderson (actor), known for "Young Dylan Rhodes Shrike" in Now You See Me 2
*Inspector William Henderson, American police official in Superman
